#ROOMS
#18150
#0T#Rh#0e #RD#0a#Rr#0k#Re#0s#Rt #0P#Ra#0r#Rt #0o#Rf #0H#Re#0l#Rl~
#0You have just entered the most ancient and evil place in all of hell.  
The walls are covered with what looks to be frozen screaming faces of 
every kind of being in the Realm. The floor is covered in a dark black 
blood, seeming to swallow you up as you step into it.  In front of you 
lies an EXTREMELY large throne, at least 15 feet high, of dark black
demonsteel and bronze.  Two massive horns grow out of the top 
corners and reach into the shadowed darkness above.  Surrounding the 
outer rim of the room are thousands of bronze candles that look to be 
burning a black and red flames.  To the right of the throne are several 
other thrones similar in color and shape but smaller in size.  To the left 
of the throne you notice a small bronze table with a darkened picture 
on top.  As you look closer you see a huge, beautiful demon, more like 
double the size of a normal demon.  Behind him is a face, a face that 
chills your bones and boils your blood, an unfamiliar face.  The face 
of Baal himself, till this moment you had no clue what he would have 
looked like, you really never wanted to find out.  Below the picture you 
see a bronze plaque which, in Demon tongue, reads "Here stands Balrok, 
Lord of Hell, Child of Baal." left and right sides of this picture are other 
pictures but only one other can be made out, the demon looks slightly 
smaller then the one in the first picture but the name says it all..... Krel.  
You try to picture the Baal in the big throne with Balrok, Krel, and Wrath 
and countless others at his side and start to grin.  If they three were to 
ever reappear you would fear, for all of the Realm would be at they're 
feet, begging for them to take their souls.  And take their souls they would.
~
